headline: Did Store Remodels and Raised Guidance Just Shift Dollar General's (DG) Investment Narrative?
summary: In recent months, Dollar General Corporation accelerated its store remodel initiatives, completing 729 Project Elevate and 592 Project Renovate upgrades, and raised its 2025 net sales growth guidance to 4.3%–4.8% as a result. This extensive investment in remodeling, covering 80% of store floor space, reflects management’s increased confidence in expected comp sales improvements and long-term growth potential.
